SpotMessanger is mod for World of Tanks.

Installation:
 - extract the archive to your game root.
 - To configure, edit [game_root]/res_mods/configs/spotmessanger/spotmessanger.xml.

where
 - [game_root] is your World of Tanks installation directory

Config
  If 'Fallback parameter' is not found in 'per BattleType parameter' section, use in 'Global Parameter' section.
 - Global parameter
     Debug
        bool: flag if enable output debug message to python.log
     ActiveByDefault
        bool: flag if enable SpotMessanger when battle startup
     ActivationHotKey
        string: key name for toggle activate SpotMessanger 
     ReloadConfigKey
        string: key name for reload config file
     ImSpotted
        string: message when spotted to send team/squad chat channel, {{pos}} is spotted position
     DisableSystemMsg
        string: message when disable mod
     EnableSystemMsg
        string: message when enable mod
     CooldownMsg
        string: message when spotted in cooldown time 
 - Fallback parameter
     CooldownInterval
        float: second of cooldown interval from last sixth sense
     TextDelay
        float: second of delay to next command
     CommandDelay
        float: second of delay to next command
 - per BattleTytpe parameter
     CommandOrder
        list: order of command when spotted, Command may ping/help/teammsg/squadmsg
     MaxTeamAmount
        int: threshold of team amount for activate sixth sense message, 0 is always active sixth sense message
     EnableVehicleType     
        list: vehicle type for enable sixth sense message, VehicleType may LT/MT/HT/TD/SPG
 